“Write once, reuse everywhere.”

📁 SHARED LIBRARY STRUCTURE (MUST MEMORIZE)
jenkins-shared-lib/
│
├── vars/
│   ├── dockerBuild.groovy
│   ├── k8sDeploy.groovy
│
└── src/
🧠 SHARED FUNCTION: dockerBuild
vars/dockerBuild.groovy
def call(String imageName) {
    sh "docker build -t ${imageName} ."
}
🧠 SHARED FUNCTION: k8sDeploy
vars/k8sDeploy.groovy
def call() {
    sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
}
🧠 ENABLE SHARED LIBRARY IN JENKINS
Jenkins →
Manage Jenkins → Configure System → Global Pipeline Libraries

Name:

devops-lib
📜 JENKINSFILE USING SHARED LIBRARY (CLEAN 🔥)
@Library('devops-lib') _

pipeline {
  agent any

  stages {

    stage('Build') {
      steps {
        dockerBuild("myapp:1")
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy') {
      steps {
        k8sDeploy()
      }
    }
  }
}
